# Phase 2: Data Integration

## Overview
This notebook integrates solar wind data with Kp index data to analyze space weather conditions. 

### Steps:
1. Load Kp index data from `Space_Weather_Indices_Subset.csv`.
2. Load and parse solar wind data from `data/solar_wind.txt` in OMNIWeb format.
3. Merge the datasets by timestamp.
4. Create visualizations to understand the relationship between solar wind properties and the Kp index.
5. Calculate correlation statistics.
6. Save the merged data and figures.

## Load Libraries
```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
```

## Load Kp Index Data
```python
# Load Kp index data
kp_data = pd.read_csv('Space_Weather_Indices_Subset.csv')
kp_data['timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(kp_data['timestamp'])
```  

## Load Solar Wind Data
```python
# Load solar wind data
df_solar_wind = pd.read_csv('data/solar_wind.txt', delim_whitespace=True)
df_solar_wind['timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df_solar_wind['Year'].astype(str) + '-' + df_solar_wind['DOY'].astype(str) + ' ' + df_solar_wind['Time'])
```

## Merge Datasets
```python
# Merge datasets based on timestamp
merged_data = pd.merge_asof(kp_data.sort_values('timestamp'), df_solar_wind.sort_values('timestamp'), on='timestamp')
```

## Create Visualizations
### 1. Kp Timeseries with Thresholds
```python
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))
sns.lineplot(data=merged_data, x='timestamp', y='Kp_index')
plt.axhline(y=4, color='r', linestyle='--') # Threshold line
plt.axhline(y=7, color='orange', linestyle='--') # Threshold line
plt.title('Kp Index Time Series with Thresholds')
plt.xlabel('Timestamp')
plt.ylabel('Kp Index')
plt.savefig('outputs/figures/kp_timeseries.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()
```

### 2. Kp vs Wind Speed
```python
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=merged_data, x='Wind Speed', y='Kp_index')
plt.title('Kp Index vs Solar Wind Speed')
plt.xlabel('Solar Wind Speed (km/s)')
plt.ylabel('Kp Index')
plt.savefig('outputs/figures/kp_vs_wind_speed.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()
```

### 3. Kp vs Bz Component
```python
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=merged_data, x='Bz', y='Kp_index')
plt.title('Kp Index vs Bz Component')
plt.xlabel('Bz Component (nT)')
plt.ylabel('Kp Index')
plt.savefig('outputs/figures/kp_vs_bz_component.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()
```

### 4. Correlation Scatter Plot
```python
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=merged_data, x='Wind Speed', y='Bz')
plt.title('Correlation Scatter Plot: Wind Speed vs Bz')
plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (km/s)')
plt.ylabel('Bz Component (nT)')
plt.savefig('outputs/figures/correlation_scatter.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()
```

### 5. Distribution Histograms
```python
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.hist(merged_data['Kp_index'], bins=30, alpha=0.7, color='blue')
plt.title('Distribution of Kp Index')
plt.xlabel('Kp Index')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.hist(merged_data['Wind Speed'], bins=30, alpha=0.7, color='orange')
plt.title('Distribution of Wind Speed')
plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (km/s)')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.savefig('outputs/figures/distribution_histograms.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()
```

## Calculate Correlation Statistics
```python
correlation = merged_data[['Kp_index', 'Wind Speed', 'Bz']].corr()
print('Correlation Statistics:')
print(correlation)
```

## Save Merged Data
```python
merged_data.to_csv('outputs/processed/space_weather_master.csv', index=False)
```

